public interface NameService<I extends Identifier>
extends QueryService<I>

NameService - 21.02.2012

A general purpose name service. This service will normally be used to aggregate PreferredNameService, SynonymService and IUPACService into a common search and fetch method. It can also be used when a database does not make a distinction between an IUPAC Name, Preferred Name or Synonym name

Method Detail

searchName

Collection<I> searchName(String name,
                         boolean approximate)
Search for the provide name. If the service provides a preferred name, IUPAC name and a synonyms all three should be search with this method

Parameters:
name - name to search for
approximate - perform a approximate search
Returns:
collection of service specific identifiers matching the provided name

getNames

Collection<String> getNames(I identifier)
Access all names for a given identifier. As with searchName, if the service provides multiple naming sub-divisions this method will return all name's for a given identifier

Parameters:
identifier - identifier to get the names for
Returns:
collection of names for the given identifier in this service
